21:11.353 --> 21:12.772
Shit.

21:14.398 --> 21:16.484
I feel like, in all that kerfuckle...

21:17.234 --> 21:19.153
I seem to have misplaced my beverages.

21:21.447 --> 21:22.447
Do you mind?

21:23.532 --> 21:26.660
- You sure that's a good idea?
- Not all ideas are good ones,

21:26.744 --> 21:29.580
but they are ideas nevertheless.

21:30.706 --> 21:32.917
Tammy, could you get me another beer?

21:33.000 --> 21:35.336
And maybe get the one
off the jukebox for me?

21:35.419 --> 21:36.712
You got it, babe.

21:40.049 --> 21:41.049
So...

21:41.550 --> 21:42.550
Michael Roth?

21:43.093 --> 21:45.429
- Yeah?
- You said you knew him?

21:45.513 --> 21:48.015
I said I knew a guy
that said he was Michael Roth.

21:49.391 --> 21:50.392
What does that mean?

21:51.685 --> 21:53.020
What does what mean?

21:53.521 --> 21:55.439
The guy who lived in your apartment
before you.

21:55.523 --> 21:57.358
The guy, the guy, um...

21:57.900 --> 21:59.276
When I moved in there,

21:59.527 --> 22:01.654
to that shithole, about six years ago,

22:01.737 --> 22:04.198
literally, that guy was gone
before he moved out.

22:04.657 --> 22:06.075
He was a Vietnam vet.

22:06.158 --> 22:07.868
Oh, yeah? What did he look like?

22:09.870 --> 22:12.039
It was six years ago.
How the fuck would I remember?

22:12.122 --> 22:14.562
- I can't remember what I said to you.
- You have to remember.

22:14.667 --> 22:16.710
- Eric, right?
- You had a conversation with him.

22:16.794 --> 22:19.964
He had hair that grew
out of the top of his head, right?

22:20.381 --> 22:23.425
He was this big, but if I was standing up,
then my hand would be higher.

22:23.509 --> 22:24.510
No, really.

22:24.593 --> 22:27.763
He had a mid skin tone.
The guy spoke English.

22:27.847 --> 22:29.932
- Run with that.
- I'm glad this is a joke to you.

22:30.015 --> 22:32.434
- Am I scaring you off?
- Enjoy the beer.

22:32.893 --> 22:34.478
Hey, Merry Christmas to you.

23:10.639 --> 23:13.267
- What the hell?
- Can we ask you some questions?

23:13.392 --> 23:14.476
About what?

23:14.977 --> 23:17.438
Hot damn! You were right, Carl.

23:17.521 --> 23:19.189
Looks like we got something here.

23:20.608 --> 23:22.067
What's going on here?

23:22.943 --> 23:24.820
Ah, looks like illegal herb.

23:26.739 --> 23:27.990
Wait, that's not mine.

23:28.115 --> 23:29.325
- No?
- No.

23:42.004 --> 23:44.089
- Well, you're in some shit now.
- What?

23:44.173 --> 23:46.926
- This is an interrogation.
- Explain this.

23:48.385 --> 23:49.637
My toilet overflowed.

23:49.720 --> 23:51.931
Oh. Why didn't you call the front desk?

23:52.014 --> 23:54.683
That's what a normal person does
when their shitter overflows.

23:54.767 --> 23:56.769
- I was gonna fix it.
- Oh, you're a plumber.

24:03.859 --> 24:05.653
- Cook crystal? See this?
- What?

24:06.946 --> 24:09.823
- This here. This is indisputable.
- No. That ain't mine.

24:09.907 --> 24:12.117
Ain't mine!
Never heard that before.

24:12.201 --> 24:13.410
I gave someone a ride.

24:13.494 --> 24:15.120
- They left it in my car.
- Oh, yeah?

24:15.204 --> 24:17.706
Okay, and who's "they"?
Do you remember his name?

24:17.873 --> 24:19.458
- <i>Charles.</i>
<i>- Charles what?</i>

24:19.583 --> 24:21.710
- Am I being charged?
- You're fixing to be.

24:21.794 --> 24:24.129
This is bullshit.
I want to speak to a lawyer.

24:24.213 --> 24:26.632
Ain't a lawyer within 50 miles of here.

24:26.715 --> 24:27.841
Plus, it's Christmas.

24:28.175 --> 24:31.720
Ah! Oh, shit, it <i>is </i> Christmas.
Merry Christmas, Carl.

24:31.804 --> 24:32.638
Shut up.

24:32.721 --> 24:34.515
What the fuck you talking about?

24:41.063 --> 24:42.356
Hey, tough guy.

24:42.940 --> 24:44.608
- Let me ask you something.
- Yeah?

24:45.734 --> 24:47.027
You running meth?

24:47.111 --> 24:48.195
- No.
- Be honest.

24:48.278 --> 24:49.446
- Ow! No!
- Be honest!

24:49.530 --> 24:51.010
Don't know what you're talking about.

24:51.073 --> 24:52.491
Drunk bastard. Stay down!

24:52.574 --> 24:53.742
Get off me, man!

24:55.285 --> 24:59.206
Oh, you think you come in this town,
peddling shit, huh?

24:59.289 --> 25:03.002
Getting our kids all strung out?
You are sorely mistaken.

25:03.335 --> 25:05.546
Ease up on him.

25:05.629 --> 25:07.339
- Ease up!
- Shut up, Billy!

25:07.589 --> 25:09.717
- Come on!
- He's running meth, and he knows it.

25:09.842 --> 25:11.282
- I'm not.
- You know you are.

25:11.343 --> 25:13.303
- You son of a bitch!
- Shit!

25:13.554 --> 25:14.722
Fuck, Carl!

25:14.805 --> 25:15.931
Why'd you do that?

25:18.642 --> 25:20.936
Merry Christmas, you drunk fucker!

25:25.149 --> 25:26.442
Fucking kids.

25:47.296 --> 25:50.591
Merry Christmas, <i>mi reina</i>.
I'm missing you a lot today.

25:52.051 --> 25:55.554
Don't worry about that Pabst girl.
She's a little too rigid for me.

26:05.647 --> 26:07.357
Oh, this damn cooler, man.

26:08.734 --> 26:09.735
¡<i>Cabrón</i>!

26:09.818 --> 26:12.321
Shit.

26:16.200 --> 26:18.077
No, no, señor.

26:26.919 --> 26:28.128
Cooler's out again?

26:28.212 --> 26:31.465
I tried that trick that you do.
I almost killed myself.

26:31.548 --> 26:34.384
- Well, you need a lady's touch.
<i>- Thank you, Katie.</i>

26:34.551 --> 26:36.720
- Okay, I'll be there in an hour.
- An hour?

26:37.262 --> 26:38.722
My beer will be piss in an hour.

26:38.806 --> 26:40.808
Okay, okay. I'll be there soon.

26:47.773 --> 26:50.109
Oh, you should ask for a raise, baby.

26:50.776 --> 26:53.362
You want something in life,
you gotta growl for it.

26:53.821 --> 26:55.447
Or do something more illicit.

26:55.531 --> 26:58.492
I am waiting for the day
you tell me I'm adopted.

26:58.575 --> 27:00.369
Well, you keep on waiting, sweetie.

27:01.370 --> 27:02.370
Uh-uh!

27:02.412 --> 27:04.623
That's for Dennis, honey.
You got your cereal.

27:05.541 --> 27:06.541
That's his name?

27:07.584 --> 27:10.170
Dennis McClarty.
All right, you can have one piece.

27:10.254 --> 27:13.966
Dennis the dental hygienist, wow.

27:14.133 --> 27:15.133
Yeah.

27:15.634 --> 27:18.846
I hope he's better at cleaning teeth
than he is at the hokey-pokey.

27:21.515 --> 27:24.268
- I thought I smelled bacon.
- Good morning.

27:24.351 --> 27:26.728
Mm!

27:26.812 --> 27:29.898
- Ooh, you brushed your teeth this morning.
- Oh, well...

27:29.982 --> 27:31.859
Your little talk scared the snot outta me.

27:32.442 --> 27:34.444
I'm gonna floss like I'm getting paid
for it.

27:34.570 --> 27:37.573
You be true to your teeth,
they'll never be false to you.

27:38.031 --> 27:40.033
Hi, Dennis McClarty.

27:40.325 --> 27:42.411
- Kate.
- Kate, that's a nice name.

27:42.494 --> 27:44.121
Who's this little guy, huh?

27:44.913 --> 27:47.332
Oh, he's the silent type, this one.

27:47.416 --> 27:49.251
Oh, well, silence is golden.

27:50.127 --> 27:52.045
Okay, I'll be back in a couple hours.

27:52.129 --> 27:53.130
Couple hours?

27:53.213 --> 27:56.133
- Well, Dennis and I were gonna go bowling.
- Yeah.

27:57.050 --> 27:58.343
But you did that last night.

27:58.427 --> 28:01.138
- Oh, we didn't make it.
- Make it.

28:01.805 --> 28:03.605
- We can take the little guy.
- Sure.

28:03.640 --> 28:05.642
- You like to bowl?
- We'll take Seth bowling.

28:05.726 --> 28:07.186
- Right?
- Oh, come on.

28:07.269 --> 28:08.312
Why you shaking your head?

28:18.155 --> 28:21.575
Mother of a bitch! Oh!

28:24.620 --> 28:25.787
Baby Jesus.

28:37.758 --> 28:38.800
Shit.

28:45.265 --> 28:46.265
Jesus.

29:13.585 --> 29:15.170
Hey. Hey!

29:15.254 --> 29:16.713
Get up. Come on, get up.

29:17.673 --> 29:20.509
Hey, put your arm down.
I'm not gonna hurt you. Sit up.

29:22.844 --> 29:23.844
Listen...

29:25.264 --> 29:26.723
you had a bag of pot.

29:26.807 --> 29:28.308
Okay? That's a fact.

29:28.850 --> 29:30.185
And you had some booze.

29:30.269 --> 29:31.561
And a bad credit card.

29:31.645 --> 29:34.064
As an officer of the law,
there's a lot to go on there.

29:34.147 --> 29:38.944
Now, in your defense,
my partner got pretty rough,

29:39.027 --> 29:42.072
and I'm sorry about that. Okay?

29:42.656 --> 29:44.324
That's not how we do things here.

29:45.742 --> 29:48.704
We're all in hot water now,
so here's what's gonna happen.

29:49.788 --> 29:52.332
I'm gonna go into the restroom,
over yonder.

29:52.416 --> 29:53.416
See that?

29:54.710 --> 29:58.505
I'm gonna put these keys,
your car keys, right there.

30:00.048 --> 30:02.301
And this is open. This is gonna be open.

30:02.884 --> 30:04.803
And I'm gonna be in the restroom.

30:05.095 --> 30:06.095
We clear?

30:09.141 --> 30:12.561
Hey, I'm gonna be in there
for quite a while.

30:19.318 --> 30:20.986
When do you get off duty?

30:22.154 --> 30:23.822
Been on duty my whole life.

30:24.156 --> 30:25.240
Every waking hour.

30:26.575 --> 30:28.243
It's been a long-ass night.

30:29.828 --> 30:31.204
You drinking that now?

30:32.998 --> 30:35.459
- Ain't it early?
- That's what I was thinking. It is...

30:35.542 --> 30:38.045
No, I mean a little early
for stupid questions.

30:39.588 --> 30:41.423
You been listening?
It's been a long night.

30:41.506 --> 30:45.052
I been listening. I just been thinking,
you shouldn't drink on the job, amigo.

30:45.135 --> 30:47.471
Maybe you should mind your own shit life.

30:48.221 --> 30:49.348
And I'll mind mine.

30:51.141 --> 30:52.142
That's all I got.

30:52.351 --> 30:53.477
I'll catch you later.

30:54.436 --> 30:55.436
Yes, sir.

30:56.355 --> 30:58.398
Glad to help
law enforcement get through the day.

30:58.482 --> 31:02.152
Yeah, yeah. <i>Feliz Navidad</i>.
Ain't that what you people say?

31:02.944 --> 31:03.987
<i>Sí, </i> señor.

31:09.242 --> 31:11.953
<i>♪ O, little town of Bethlehem♪</i>

31:12.746 --> 31:15.332
<i>♪ How still we see thee lie ♪</i>

31:15.415 --> 31:16.415
What'd he want?

31:17.376 --> 31:18.627
What he always wants.

31:18.960 --> 31:21.463
Vicente, you can't let him run
all over you like that.

31:21.546 --> 31:25.008
He won't be around much longer.
His demons are catching up to him.

31:25.926 --> 31:26.927
How's my man doing?

31:27.969 --> 31:30.180
Santa Claus came
to Vicente's early this year.

31:33.308 --> 31:34.393
Go on. Open it.

31:36.353 --> 31:37.479
Oh, what is it?

31:37.771 --> 31:39.231
Oh...

31:39.314 --> 31:42.192
I got some batteries in the back.
Go get 'em, huh? Come on.

32:15.976 --> 32:16.977
The fuck?

32:26.194 --> 32:29.197
<i>♪ We got married in a Walmart ♪</i>

32:30.157 --> 32:33.702
<i>♪ Down by the Wrangler jeans ♪</i>

32:35.370 --> 32:36.621
Shit.

32:37.205 --> 32:39.332
Billy, Billy come in.

32:41.001 --> 32:42.627
<i>Billy, where are you?</i>

32:43.420 --> 32:46.548
<i>♪ Got a lot of things
Down at the Walmart ♪</i>

32:47.382 --> 32:49.885
<i>♪ Things like trampolines ♪</i>

32:49.968 --> 32:51.761
Get over, get over!

32:51.845 --> 32:52.888
Get over, now!

32:56.766 --> 32:57.766
Shit!

32:58.143 --> 33:00.854
<i>♪ Yes, I'm a ballerina ♪</i>

33:00.937 --> 33:02.814
<i>♪ A ballerina ♪</i>

33:04.483 --> 33:05.692
Shit!

33:05.775 --> 33:06.985
What the fuck?

33:10.614 --> 33:13.492
<i>♪ A ballerina on the lam ♪</i>

33:20.499 --> 33:23.585
<i>♪ We got married in a Walmart ♪</i>

33:24.252 --> 33:27.672
<i>♪ Down by the franks and beans ♪</i>

33:28.215 --> 33:30.133
<i>♪ Killed a guy in Texas ♪</i>

33:37.891 --> 33:40.810
<i>♪ Makin' love
And then we're makin' bacon ♪</i>

33:41.603 --> 33:45.357
<i>♪ Just wipe down the Foreman grill ♪</i>

33:45.649 --> 33:49.402
<i>♪ Lookee there, Bocephus, over yonder♪</i>

33:49.486 --> 33:52.572
<i>♪ That's where your pappy was killed♪</i>

33:52.656 --> 33:57.160
<i>♪ Yes, I'm a ballerina, a ballerina ♪</i>

33:57.244 --> 34:02.999
<i>♪ Ballerina on the lam
Ballerina, ballerina ♪</i>

34:05.377 --> 34:08.797
<i>♪ Ballerina, ballerina ♪</i>

34:14.844 --> 34:16.054
Damn you.

34:16.221 --> 34:18.431
Billy, God damn you, Billy.

34:19.014 --> 34:21.184
Billy, I swear to God, I'll kill you.

34:21.476 --> 34:24.563
One day, you're gonna die,
and I ain't gonna give a shit.

34:25.146 --> 34:29.359
<i>I swear on your mother.</i>

34:29.442 --> 34:33.280
<i>Clue me in how that little son of a bitch
got outta jail. Clue me in!</i>

34:38.868 --> 34:40.954
- Merry Christmas, Larry.
- Yeah, spare me.

34:42.789 --> 34:44.248
Yeah. Mm-hmm.

34:44.958 --> 34:46.126
Beer's not cold.

34:46.793 --> 34:48.920
Well, I am used to struggle.

35:01.516 --> 35:02.892
Ah, shit.

35:10.275 --> 35:13.194
Shit.

35:15.530 --> 35:20.493
How about the Jack, the Seven, and give me
that last Wild Turkey you have,

35:20.577 --> 35:23.079
and give me a half dozen
of your daily scratchers.

35:25.040 --> 35:29.169
Why don't you find yourself a good lady?
You wouldn't need all this liquor, Larry.

35:29.252 --> 35:32.172
This is how it works.
I give you money, you give me booze.

35:32.339 --> 35:33.757
It's just simple capitalism.

35:36.718 --> 35:39.137
- Why don't you grab a six-pack, on me?
- No shit?

35:39.262 --> 35:40.847
Trying to spread some cheer, bro.

35:42.390 --> 35:45.852
Look at that.
It's a Merry Christmas after all.

35:57.781 --> 35:59.282
Shots fired!

35:59.658 --> 36:01.868
<i>Shots fired</i>
<i>at Vicente's Liquor Mart!</i>

36:01.951 --> 36:03.411
<i>Billy, get your ass over here!</i>

36:08.375 --> 36:09.709
I can't get it to work.

36:14.756 --> 36:16.049
Get down! Get down!

36:16.508 --> 36:18.218
- Seth!
- Keep your head down!

36:19.803 --> 36:21.638
Ah, shit!

36:21.763 --> 36:24.099
Goddamn! What did you do that for?

36:24.182 --> 36:25.350
It's military, asshole.

36:26.059 --> 36:28.186
You fire a gun at me, I'm gonna fire back.

36:28.269 --> 36:30.063
I wasn't shooting at you!

36:31.189 --> 36:33.858
- We got a fugitive right there.
- No, no, no, no.

36:33.942 --> 36:35.193
Your partner let me go.

36:35.276 --> 36:38.279
Yeah, you tell that to the judge.

36:38.363 --> 36:42.617
And you... you, hey! Hey! You're going
to jail for attempted murder.

36:42.701 --> 36:45.036
I aimed at your goddamn leg,
I hit you in the goddamn leg.

36:45.120 --> 36:47.872
That's what it looks like
when someone's not trying to kill you.

36:47.956 --> 36:50.125
- Hey, put that away.
- No, no, no, no!

36:50.792 --> 36:53.086
I ain't putting it down! Shut the fuck up!

36:53.169 --> 36:54.754
- Put it away!
- No!

36:56.464 --> 36:59.050
You listen, you're in deep shit.

36:59.134 --> 37:00.176
You got that?

37:00.260 --> 37:01.761
Now, you let everyone go,

37:01.845 --> 37:05.181
- and I promise you due process of law.
- I'm not holding anybody.

37:05.265 --> 37:07.600
Yeah, this is some fucked-up shit.
Look, I'm done.

37:07.684 --> 37:09.561
I'm out of this. I'm out of this.

37:09.936 --> 37:11.146
Hey, hey, hey!

37:11.229 --> 37:14.149
Hey, we don't want
a hostage situation here.

37:14.232 --> 37:15.692
God damn...

37:16.443 --> 37:17.443
you.

37:17.694 --> 37:19.988
Listen, I've got backup coming.

37:20.113 --> 37:23.616
You calm down
and we will talk this out.

37:23.700 --> 37:25.034
Oh, shit.

37:31.666 --> 37:33.460
- Sheriff's Department!
- Fuck.

37:33.543 --> 37:34.753
What's going on?

37:34.836 --> 37:38.298
- Put that shit down and crawl outta here.
- I ain't putting it down!

37:38.381 --> 37:41.634
- Put it down and get out! Now!
- How the hell am I supposed to get out?

37:41.760 --> 37:43.803
God damn it! How am I supposed to move?

37:48.141 --> 37:50.101
- Shit. Shit.
- Damn, damn. Listen.

37:51.436 --> 37:52.562
Hell's going on?

37:52.645 --> 37:55.774
Shut these blinds before RoboCop
out there fires another warning shot.

37:55.857 --> 37:57.984
- Close the blinds!
- Now! Go!

37:58.943 --> 38:02.238
- What's Carl doing all over the radio?
- It was shots fired, Sheriff!

38:02.322 --> 38:03.490
I know that, Billy!

38:03.573 --> 38:05.742
- Who the hell's firing?
- Get him away from the door.

38:05.825 --> 38:07.577
Okay. But I'm not an accessory, man.

38:07.660 --> 38:10.830
Carl was after a suspect.
Could be this kid we picked up.

38:10.914 --> 38:14.667
Who'd you pick up? Are you two
playing cops and robbers again?

38:15.752 --> 38:16.752
Billy.

38:19.589 --> 38:21.629
- You're holding us here?
- Everyone shut up!

38:21.674 --> 38:24.677
Just... just shut up and sit down.

38:25.428 --> 38:28.264
- I just need a minute to think.
- It's okay, honey.

38:29.140 --> 38:31.559
Now, do we know exactly who's in there?

38:31.976 --> 38:34.354
Not exactly, sir.

38:34.771 --> 38:36.439
I believe there's Carl.

38:36.523 --> 38:37.774
Hey, stop it.

38:38.566 --> 38:40.568
Come here. God damn it!

38:40.777 --> 38:42.445
Probably likely Vicente.

38:43.446 --> 38:46.658
And then, I'm guessing,
the kid we picked up. I think.

38:47.116 --> 38:48.116
Or not.

38:50.453 --> 38:52.205
- What's the plan?
- I'm gonna go in back.

38:52.288 --> 38:53.581
Okay, okay.

38:53.915 --> 38:55.542
Okay, okay.

38:55.625 --> 38:56.625
I got you.

38:57.001 --> 38:58.628
Criminal punk bastard.

38:58.753 --> 39:01.256
- Will you just shut the fuck up?
- You shut the fuck up!

39:01.339 --> 39:03.299
- Stop pointing that.
- Where are your handcuffs?

39:03.383 --> 39:05.802
Go to hell! God! Shit!

39:05.885 --> 39:07.846
Get 'em out. Get 'em out!

39:08.888 --> 39:10.390
Everybody be cool!

39:10.473 --> 39:12.225
Put your handcuffs on!

39:12.851 --> 39:16.104
- Is there a back way out?
- A window, but you won't fit through it.

39:16.187 --> 39:18.731
<i>Nobody moves, okay? Okay?</i>

39:19.607 --> 39:20.733
<i>God damn it!</i>

39:22.235 --> 39:26.281
Come out with your hands up!
You're... mostly surrounded!

39:52.640 --> 39:54.434
Freeze!

39:54.517 --> 39:56.769
- Shit!
- Shots fired! Shots fired!

40:00.690 --> 40:01.774
Oh, shit!

40:02.442 --> 40:04.068
God damn it.

40:07.614 --> 40:09.574
Taking fire, Sheriff! Taking fire!

40:09.699 --> 40:10.699
Returning fire!

40:12.702 --> 40:14.704
Damn it.

40:14.787 --> 40:15.997
Sheriff taking fire.

40:19.918 --> 40:21.461
- Everyone all right?
- It's okay.

40:21.544 --> 40:22.587
I got you. Just hold me.

40:22.670 --> 40:24.339
Quite a police force you got.

40:24.422 --> 40:26.049
Yeah. They're shooting at each other.

40:27.300 --> 40:28.384
Returning fire!

40:28.509 --> 40:30.595
Sheriff return...

40:33.848 --> 40:35.099
Wait... wait a minute.

40:36.726 --> 40:37.726
Stop firing.

40:37.810 --> 40:39.395
Yes, returning fire!

40:41.397 --> 40:42.565
Stand down.

40:42.815 --> 40:43.815
Man down?

40:43.858 --> 40:49.572
No, not "man down"!
Stand down! <i>Stand </i> down!

40:49.656 --> 40:54.285
- <i>Stop firing. You a fucking idiot?</i>
- Oh, okay. Stand down.

40:58.748 --> 41:00.750
Whatever your name is,
please just...

41:00.833 --> 41:02.502
His name is Eric Norris.

41:03.169 --> 41:05.088
Been running drugs out of Missouri.

41:05.171 --> 41:07.048
Picked him up last night. He's a fugitive.

41:07.131 --> 41:09.884
Now he can add kidnapping,
hit-and-run, and attempted murder!

41:09.968 --> 41:11.094
That's bullshit.

41:11.844 --> 41:13.930
Him and his partner arrested me
for no reason.

41:14.013 --> 41:17.392
That ain't true. He had weed
and crystal meth paraphernalia.

41:17.475 --> 41:19.310
I had Drano. And the weed was his.

41:19.394 --> 41:22.397
They beat the shit out of me
for trying to unclog a toilet.

41:23.064 --> 41:25.900
- You think I did this to myself?
- You're such a dick, Carl.

41:25.984 --> 41:28.653
What? You're gonna listen to him?

41:28.987 --> 41:29.987
Look at him.

41:30.780 --> 41:31.864
Then look at me.

41:34.659 --> 41:35.743
Sheriff, Sheriff!

41:35.868 --> 41:36.868
Sheriff!

41:41.833 --> 41:43.042
What are we gonna do?

41:49.424 --> 41:51.509
We're gonna get a time machine, Billy.

41:52.677 --> 41:54.554
And I'm gonna go back in time

41:55.054 --> 41:57.932
to when my cousin was dating your mother.

41:58.933 --> 42:01.060
And then I'm gonna yank his pecker off,

42:01.144 --> 42:04.397
right before he has the chance
to create an idiot.

42:19.996 --> 42:21.205
My guess is, that's for you.

42:30.298 --> 42:31.883
Hello?

42:32.467 --> 42:36.095
Well, looks like we got a situation here.

42:36.179 --> 42:37.179
Yeah.

42:37.722 --> 42:38.890
Yeah, I'd say we do.

42:40.558 --> 42:43.038
You're shooting up the place,
and there's innocent people here.

42:43.102 --> 42:44.395
Who am I talking to here?

42:44.812 --> 42:46.189
- This the suspect?
- No.

42:47.023 --> 42:48.816
The suspect's your guy
in here on the floor.

42:48.900 --> 42:49.900
Hey.

42:50.526 --> 42:52.153
You talking about Carl Hooker?

42:52.653 --> 42:53.654
Yeah, that's him.

42:55.531 --> 42:58.284
- Why the hell are you shooting at us?
- I'll tell you what.

42:58.659 --> 43:00.745
Why don't you come out,
and we'll talk about it?

43:01.204 --> 43:02.997
I promise you that you'll be safe.

43:03.081 --> 43:04.248
<i>Yeah, I trust you.</i>

43:04.332 --> 43:06.709
Every cop in this fucking town's insane.

43:11.130 --> 43:13.841
Now, when Jesus was born
in Bethlehem of Judea,

43:14.383 --> 43:16.677
wise men from the East came to Jerusalem,

43:16.761 --> 43:20.014
saying, "Where is he that is born
king of the Jews?

43:20.098 --> 43:23.101
For we have seen a star in the east,
and have come to worship him."

43:23.935 --> 43:25.478
Elias, say your line.

43:25.895 --> 43:27.563
Fear not, baby God.

43:28.147 --> 43:32.193
Lo, the star, which they saw
in the east, went before them.

43:32.276 --> 43:35.571
Until it came and stood over
where the young child was.

43:35.988 --> 43:39.450
When they saw the star, they rejoiced
with exceeding great joy.

43:40.159 --> 43:41.994
When they came into the house,

43:42.078 --> 43:45.039
they saw a young child
with Mary, his mother.

44:02.181 --> 44:04.892
<i>...law enforcement officers yesterday.</i>

44:05.017 --> 44:06.686
<i>Damn it, we have a situation.</i>

44:06.769 --> 44:09.897
<i>...inside Vicente's Liquor Mart.</i>

44:10.773 --> 44:12.608
- Come on!
- Let's go.

44:13.484 --> 44:15.153
This is the situation.

44:15.820 --> 44:19.657
Now, Carl, he radioed in
before he entered the place.

44:20.199 --> 44:23.703
But he never said who he was chasing,
or for what reason.

44:24.203 --> 44:28.124
We have no idea
where all these hostages are located.

44:28.207 --> 44:29.959
They could be
back by the liquor cabinet.

44:30.042 --> 44:31.586
They could be
there by the ice machine,

44:31.669 --> 44:34.630
they could be back there
in the crapper, or in Vicente's office.

44:35.131 --> 44:39.802
Hell, we don't even know who are
the hostages and who's the hostage-taker.

44:40.803 --> 44:44.974
Now, you said that you thought maybe
that this kid you arrested,

44:45.057 --> 44:47.226
- that he could be the gunman?
- Yes. Yes.

44:47.518 --> 44:49.145
I mean, I'm fairly certain.

44:49.478 --> 44:54.358
Although, I...
I do believe I saw two white males,

44:54.442 --> 44:56.444
twenties, duck behind the counter.

44:57.028 --> 45:01.199
And... I mean, this one's...
This is crazy,

45:01.282 --> 45:04.160
but I... I thought I saw a little kid.

45:05.745 --> 45:06.787
Jesus, Billy.

45:07.371 --> 45:08.206
Are you sure?

45:08.289 --> 45:11.709
I can't be positively positive for sure.

45:11.792 --> 45:13.169
But I... I'll tell you this.

45:13.252 --> 45:15.463
There's definitely four or five folks
in there, maybe.

45:16.172 --> 45:20.218
Well, this is a clusterfuck.

45:21.177 --> 45:24.388
All right, Billy...
you're the second-in-command.

45:25.264 --> 45:26.891
I want you to find out all you can.

45:26.974 --> 45:30.186
And make sure
that you secure this entire area.

45:30.311 --> 45:31.479
You got that?

45:31.938 --> 45:33.105
Absolutely, boss.

45:33.606 --> 45:35.233
Second-in-command, let's do this.

45:46.953 --> 45:47.953
Is he okay?

45:48.871 --> 45:50.623
You got yourself in a real mess here.

45:51.207 --> 45:52.847
What's your game plan?

45:52.917 --> 45:54.961
I'm just trying not to get anybody killed.

45:55.044 --> 45:58.172
Then put your gun down, your hands up,
and walk outside.

45:58.256 --> 46:00.258
No, no, that would be a bad idea.

46:01.425 --> 46:04.387
Whoever walks out that door
becomes a target.

46:04.804 --> 46:05.972
I've seen this before.

46:06.597 --> 46:07.682
Doesn't end well.

46:08.182 --> 46:10.559
You think you're right.
He thinks you're wrong.

46:11.352 --> 46:12.353
You lose.

46:13.020 --> 46:14.438
Then let me state the obvious.

46:14.522 --> 46:17.942
You, sir, have shot
a law enforcement officer.

46:18.276 --> 46:20.194
And you, you think you're not a criminal?

46:20.528 --> 46:22.655
I've never heard of good people
that hold hostages.

46:22.738 --> 46:25.533
And you shooting at my car,
trying to kill me. What's that?

46:25.616 --> 46:27.243
That is my word against yours.

46:27.326 --> 46:28.869
You see how this works now?

46:40.589 --> 46:41.589
Okay.

46:43.634 --> 46:45.511
Okay!

46:46.721 --> 46:48.014
Here's what we know for certain.

46:48.848 --> 46:52.268
Vicente Santos is the owner
of Vicente's Liquor Mart,

46:52.893 --> 46:55.104
and as such, he's probably on the scene.

46:55.938 --> 46:58.441
I think maybe Kate Daniels
is working the counter today.

46:58.524 --> 47:00.818
I called her house
and didn't get an answer, so...

47:00.901 --> 47:03.112
I'd deduce she's inside as well.

47:03.738 --> 47:05.698
Which led me to further deduce...

47:06.532 --> 47:09.410
that the little boy inside,
if in fact there is a little boy,

47:09.493 --> 47:10.953
probably her son, Seth.

47:11.037 --> 47:12.037
Okay.

47:13.289 --> 47:15.416
Run the plates on all these vehicles here.

47:15.916 --> 47:17.084
Already did that.

47:17.168 --> 47:20.463
First, we got Vicente's pickup truck,
the blue Dodge.

47:20.921 --> 47:24.050
You got that little shitbox import,
that's Kate Daniels' car.

47:24.258 --> 47:26.052
Carl's patrol vehicle's down the road,

47:26.135 --> 47:28.637
and it appears to have been
in some kind of altercation.

47:29.055 --> 47:31.307
And then we have the Chevelle.

47:31.932 --> 47:32.975
That's Eric Norris'.

47:33.059 --> 47:36.729
Now that's the suspect
that Carl and I tangled with last night.

47:37.146 --> 47:39.315
He may or may not be the hostage-taker.

47:41.067 --> 47:43.277
- Did you hit your head or something?
- No.

47:43.569 --> 47:45.905
You're starting to act
like a damn police officer.

47:48.074 --> 47:49.867
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

47:49.950 --> 47:52.244
You want me to re-establish contact
with the inside?

47:52.328 --> 47:54.663
No. I just want to sit here
and think for a minute.

47:55.414 --> 47:58.793
All right, 'cause I could function
as a negotiator,

47:58.876 --> 48:00.836
establish a rapport maybe.

48:01.337 --> 48:03.089
It's not a damn movie, Billy.

48:04.256 --> 48:06.258
You're not Samuel fucking Jackson.

48:15.476 --> 48:16.936
Wow. Look at that.

48:18.062 --> 48:19.438
This is cool.

48:21.649 --> 48:22.691
Man, looks bad.

48:23.609 --> 48:24.609
Yeah.

48:27.988 --> 48:29.281
<i>It's a security camera.</i>

48:29.448 --> 48:32.243
Yeah, everything's on tape.

48:32.326 --> 48:35.204
<i>You with my gun, and you shooting at me.</i>

48:35.287 --> 48:37.927
- You're on it too, asshole.
- Hey, where are the controls?

48:38.416 --> 48:39.625
My office in the back.

48:39.708 --> 48:42.128
- I'll show you where they are.
- I'll show him.

48:44.338 --> 48:45.381
Fine.

48:51.303 --> 48:53.347
Holy shit, they're everywhere.

48:53.431 --> 48:54.974
Yeah, is that a surprise?

48:56.016 --> 48:57.852
Oh, God.

49:01.355 --> 49:02.898
Look, you want my advice?

49:03.190 --> 49:05.693
If you didn't do anything,
just turn yourself in.

49:06.318 --> 49:09.738
Turn myself in? To the same cops
that are shooting at us for no reason?

49:09.822 --> 49:12.408
Yeah. You're holding two old men
and my child hostage.

49:12.491 --> 49:13.784
At least let them go.

49:14.243 --> 49:16.579
I will. I'm gonna let you all go. I swear.

49:17.079 --> 49:18.706
What are you doing here anyway?

49:18.789 --> 49:20.249
What'd you come here for?

49:21.459 --> 49:22.293
To find someone.

49:22.376 --> 49:23.919
- Yeah? Who?
- A man.

49:24.003 --> 49:25.546
- What man?
- Does it really matter?

49:25.629 --> 49:26.881
Yeah, it does matter.

49:29.925 --> 49:31.427
My father used to live here.

49:32.136 --> 49:33.137
Or he still does.

49:33.262 --> 49:35.681
I don't know, so I came here
to try and find him.

49:36.140 --> 49:37.641
What, and you've never met him?

49:37.725 --> 49:39.143
No, I've never met him.

49:40.269 --> 49:43.230
Thought it might be a good time,
being Christmas and all, but,

49:43.355 --> 49:46.192
in hindsight,
that wasn't such a good idea.

49:53.073 --> 49:54.867
Oh, goody, goody, TV.

49:55.326 --> 49:57.661
We can watch <i>Die Hard</i>.
That's a great Christmas movie.

49:58.871 --> 50:01.332
Vicente's Hostage Mart. Merry Christmas!

50:01.415 --> 50:03.334
- I'm not talking to them.
- Mm...

50:11.342 --> 50:13.010
Hey, what are you doing?

50:14.261 --> 50:15.095
Talk to me.

50:15.179 --> 50:18.182
You got 30 minutes
to release all hostages.

50:18.432 --> 50:22.561
If you don't release them,
we are gonna gas this place.

50:23.145 --> 50:27.233
I advise that you surrender any women
and children forthwith.

50:27.316 --> 50:29.276
You done yakking? Now listen up!

50:29.360 --> 50:31.946
Okay, and who is this?

50:32.071 --> 50:34.615
- The guy you're talking to.
- Don't say anything stupid.

50:34.698 --> 50:36.367
Are you a hostage?

50:37.034 --> 50:38.869
We want money, lots of money.

50:39.370 --> 50:41.539
Do-re-mi. Big bills.

50:41.622 --> 50:45.042
Christmastime, we didn't get any packages,
we're all pissed off in here.

50:45.125 --> 50:47.336
Unmarked
and none of that blue dye or anything.

50:47.419 --> 50:48.420
Bye.

50:52.007 --> 50:53.008
Seriously?

50:53.634 --> 50:55.010
What the fuck is wrong with you?

50:55.553 --> 50:58.806
- I have always wanted to do that.
- You're out of your goddamn mind.

50:58.931 --> 51:01.475
- You better call them back.
- They're at 911.

51:01.559 --> 51:04.270
- They're gonna think you're part of this.
- They're not.

51:04.353 --> 51:05.896
It's a bunch of dumb shits out there.

51:06.313 --> 51:07.773
Well, that was an older man.

51:08.274 --> 51:10.317
That wasn't that kid I spoke to earlier.

51:10.401 --> 51:12.111
You saying it was an older man?

51:13.237 --> 51:14.613
That's what I just said.

51:15.114 --> 51:17.616
- Okay.
- So, who the hell is who in there?

51:17.950 --> 51:19.451
Well, here's what we know.

51:19.577 --> 51:22.955
Vicente Santos is the owner
of Santos Liquor Mart, and as such...

51:23.038 --> 51:27.334
Damn it, I know what you got written
in your little notebook there, Sherlock.

51:28.210 --> 51:30.713
That wasn't Vicente,
and it sure as hell wasn't Carl.

51:30.796 --> 51:32.840
Well, I don't have a vehicle
for an old-timer.

51:32.965 --> 51:36.260
- I got Vicente's blue pickup...
- Did you talk to that reporter yet?

51:36.635 --> 51:38.596
- No.
- What the hell you waiting for?

51:38.721 --> 51:39.721
Okay.

51:46.270 --> 51:47.313
I'm hungry.

51:47.521 --> 51:48.814
I think we should eat.

51:48.897 --> 51:50.691
The peanuts just aren't doing it.

51:50.774 --> 51:52.359
Come on. What do you say?

51:53.485 --> 51:56.655
We are live, outside
of Vicente's Liquor Mart in El Camino,

51:56.739 --> 52:00.200
<i>in the midst of what appears
to be a hostage situation</i>

52:00.284 --> 52:01.952
<i>on Christmas Eve.</i>

52:02.036 --> 52:05.289
<i>Authorities cannot confirm the identities
of the hostages.</i>

52:05.372 --> 52:08.125
- <i>However, Action 19 News has learned...</i>
- Oh, my grace.

52:08.208 --> 52:11.086
<i>...that Deputy Carl Hooker,
of El Camino's sheriff's department,</i>

52:11.211 --> 52:12.963
<i>is trapped inside the mart.</i>

52:28.562 --> 52:32.024
So, Carl, why don't you tell us
what really happened last night?

52:32.107 --> 52:35.235
You'll find out in court,
or at his funeral.

52:35.361 --> 52:36.945
He don't know the truth at this point.

52:38.030 --> 52:39.030
Come on.

52:39.823 --> 52:40.991
Give us the truth.

52:41.075 --> 52:43.369
- We're all friends here.
- What good is the truth?

52:43.452 --> 52:45.537
The truth will set you free.

52:45.663 --> 52:46.538
Set us free.

52:46.622 --> 52:49.208
I mean, you're a drunk, we all know that.

52:49.291 --> 52:51.001
- It's a small town.
- You're a drunk.

52:51.126 --> 52:52.920
Yeah, but I don't hide behind a badge.

52:53.170 --> 52:54.546
I don't drink and drive.

52:57.549 --> 52:58.676
You ran a red light.

53:00.344 --> 53:03.097
- He had narcotics in his system.
- Yeah?

53:04.556 --> 53:07.976
- What'd you have in your system?
- Had a little blonde girl in my system.

53:08.102 --> 53:09.436
How about that? Ha!

53:09.520 --> 53:11.647
- That's disgusting.
- Tell you what, Carl.

53:13.273 --> 53:15.442
Tell everybody here
what really happened last night,

53:15.526 --> 53:17.861
and I'll walk outside
and surrender right now.

53:28.580 --> 53:30.340
<i>Is there anything else</i>
<i>you can tell us</i>

53:30.416 --> 53:32.710
about the people in the store
when you were shopping?

53:32.793 --> 53:33.794
Not really.

53:35.295 --> 53:36.295
Hello, ma'am.

53:37.005 --> 53:40.926
I'm with the sheriff's department.
Oh, my! They hide that well on TV.

53:41.176 --> 53:42.803
- Beth Flowers.
- Oh, I know.

53:43.011 --> 53:44.096
Billy Calhoun.

53:44.221 --> 53:45.639
Deputy Billy Calhoun.

53:45.723 --> 53:48.475
Second-in-command here on the scene.

53:49.017 --> 53:51.145
May I ask you a few questions?

53:51.270 --> 53:53.939
- Yes, ma'am. That's why I'm here.
- Fantastic.

53:55.649 --> 53:59.945
<i>Deputy Calhoun, do you have any idea
who the gunman is?</i>

54:00.112 --> 54:02.489
<i>Do you have a name? A suspect?</i>

54:03.240 --> 54:06.493
<i>Uh, well, me and my partner and I,</i>

54:06.577 --> 54:09.663
<i>Deputy Carl Hooker, H-O-O-K-E-R,</i>

54:09.747 --> 54:13.584
<i>- arrested a young man last night.</i>
<i>- And what was he arrested for?</i>

54:13.667 --> 54:16.962
He was drug running.

54:17.796 --> 54:19.298
Methamphetamine, we imagine.

54:19.381 --> 54:23.552
We had the suspect, Mr. Eric Norris,

54:23.635 --> 54:27.639
<i>under surveillance
because he fit a profile</i>

54:27.723 --> 54:29.475
<i>- with a gold credit card.
- Eric Norris...</i>

54:29.558 --> 54:30.809
<i>- Drano.
- ...you said?</i>

54:30.893 --> 54:32.436
<i>Well, it's just a feeling you get</i>

54:32.519 --> 54:34.772
<i>when you've been doing this
as long as we have.</i>

54:34.855 --> 54:36.315
<i>It's like a sixth sense.</i>

54:36.440 --> 54:37.775
<i>- Off the record.
- Right.</i>

54:38.066 --> 54:39.066
<i>Right.</i>

54:40.068 --> 54:44.156
So, the suspect posts bail
and was released?

54:44.823 --> 54:46.283
Not exactly. No, ma'am.

54:48.619 --> 54:49.912
<i>He escaped.</i>

54:51.288 --> 54:53.624
- Escaped from?
- From our facilities.

54:53.707 --> 54:54.707
<i>County jail?</i>

54:55.167 --> 54:56.167
<i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

54:57.002 --> 54:58.837
<i>How does that happen, exactly?</i>

55:00.297 --> 55:01.548
<i>You know, we just...</i>

55:01.632 --> 55:03.467
<i>We want to get everyone
outta here safely,</i>

55:03.550 --> 55:07.054
<i>and reunited with their loved ones
before this very special holiday.</i>

55:08.639 --> 55:10.808
<i>All right. This is Beth Flowers
reporting from...</i>

55:10.891 --> 55:13.644
<i>If you have any further questions,
I will be on scene.</i>

55:14.228 --> 55:15.354
<i>Just look for...</i>

55:16.396 --> 55:17.396
<i>Okay.</i>

55:17.731 --> 55:22.361
<i>This is Beth Flowers, reporting live
from Vicente's Liquor Mart.</i>

55:27.324 --> 55:29.576
I'm gonna need some medical attention.

55:31.078 --> 55:32.078
Start talking.

55:33.831 --> 55:36.625
Oh, you're gonna have a dead cop
on your hands,

55:36.708 --> 55:38.377
you don't get me out of here soon.

55:38.460 --> 55:41.505
That's... that's life in prison.

55:42.798 --> 55:43.798
He's right.

55:44.466 --> 55:45.466
Dead pig...

55:46.093 --> 55:47.177
<i>no es bueno</i>.

55:49.638 --> 55:51.181
I just want my life back.

55:52.140 --> 55:55.227
I wanna rewind before I ever came here.
You can do that.

55:59.106 --> 56:01.400
I'm just gonna tell them what happened.

56:01.483 --> 56:02.483
You know?

56:03.485 --> 56:05.112
Everybody's got their own truth.

56:05.195 --> 56:06.613
- You know?
- Yeah.

56:08.657 --> 56:10.158
Only one of them's right.

56:10.242 --> 56:11.660
Only God knows.

56:12.786 --> 56:15.497
He probably knows you don't know shit.

56:15.998 --> 56:18.250
The fuck you know, Vicente.

56:20.460 --> 56:22.588
Remember when your alarm went off?

56:24.548 --> 56:26.800
I was the first one to arrive here.

56:28.385 --> 56:29.385
You were home...

56:30.804 --> 56:32.347
taking care of your sick wife.

56:32.431 --> 56:33.431
Remember?

56:35.475 --> 56:37.686
Huh? I saved your business.

56:45.027 --> 56:46.153
And you, blondie.

56:48.822 --> 56:50.657
Who'd you come running to...

56:51.867 --> 56:54.328
when your boyfriend
was slapping you around?

56:55.037 --> 56:56.037
Hmm?

56:57.748 --> 57:00.042
I ran that ingrate outta town.

57:05.839 --> 57:07.758
And you, you fucking drunk,

57:08.258 --> 57:11.053
with your goddamn Vietnam sob story.

57:20.520 --> 57:22.481
I been cleaning all your messes.

57:22.940 --> 57:23.941
All y'all's.

57:30.113 --> 57:31.406
See, that's my truth.

57:36.411 --> 57:38.121
You, son, are a bad seed.

57:41.375 --> 57:43.669
I'm just doing my job.

57:46.838 --> 57:48.006
What's your truth?

58:02.938 --> 58:04.564
My mom passed away.

